<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#00ff00" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">cjd</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Anyone that wants to share info on quests that either give great exp or a high reward for the level of it, post away.  I'll start off with a couple I can think of off the top of my head.<P>Level 3 - 6: Kaladim - In the cleric area, the bone chip quest.  Turn in four chips (stacked ok) to Gunlok Jure, get quite a bit of exp.  I've gone from 3 to 6 (killing NPCs is easy enough to get through 1 and 2) with about two backpacks of bone chips.  Once you turn 7, the amount of exp dwindles down significantly.<P>Level 3 - 7?: Qeynos - Turn in rabid wolf pelts to Caulria (I think?).  Again, these come up with a lot of exp.  The wolves are level 3-5.  Later (10 or so) you can do the same with rabid bears for another significant exp boost.<P>Level 8 - 12: North Karana (good)/ South Ro (evil) - The old stand-by money-maker in the early part of the game, willowisps.  They are about level 8-11.  So it's reasonable exp for making the kill, then turn in GLSes to the gypsy camps for the 8-10p book.  I had a corpse decay on one young character I didn't play for a few months, and used this to reoutfit him in a relatively short time.<P>Level 1 - ?: Paineel - I haven't done this one in a long time, but it is the history books quest.  One of the three books sells for around one gold (the other two only sell for a few copper).  Just say the phrase to the NPC, collect a billion books, cash them in to any vendor.  As you can imagine, it is quite tedious.<P>Level 30ish rogues, the Burning Rapier quest.  I did this one just after hitting 30 (cursed hell levels!) and wound up getting half of level 30's exp for it all.  There were about 3 pieces of the quest that each gave around 500k exp.  I don't know if others can go through the quest, or if you could repeat one of those pieces over and over for the easy 500k.  It's been too long for my memory.  <IMG SRC="http://www.ethernalquest.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Of course with anything like these, you will have to spend as much time working on skills as you do repeating the quests.<P>Others?<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ImJust_a_Gnome</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">you can find any quest you want for the most part on allakhazam. http://everquest.allakhazam.com/<BR>can even list em by  zone they start in or lvl range class faction.  posting them here would pretty much just be a jumbled mess. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">equilizer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Don't forget about getting GLs's and turning them in to gypsy's in south ro, get great exp till about 11 or 12 and get about 8 or 9 plat per.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bio_War</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Unfortunatly the history book in Paineel was fucked up not to long ago by those bastard loosers that like to ruin this game, and is now only worth 1cp or so.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mikeb4kool</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I forget, but I might have been the one who first spoke up about the paineel books here. Only because I managed to macro the process.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">cjd</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Duh, there are a few thousand web pages that list all quests.  But they don't tell ya exactly how much exp you get for them, like we can here with SEQ.<P>For instance, working from memory (haven't sat down and did the quests in a while), the rabid wolf quests give about 4000 exp points.  Considiring you get about 1500 for killing the wolf, that's an extra 2+ kills for free.<P>The GLS quest (when you're in appropriate level range) is about 7500 exp points per try; the equivilent of about 1 extra kill.<P>Many of the quests I've done have server-side level limits.  As you advance, you get more exp points until some peak, then it quickly diminishes.  I suppose it's their attempt to prevent level 1's from doing something like the Burning Rapier and making several levels in one shot.<P>Speaking of the BR quest, after pondering about it since the last post, I believe the part of killing Lynada and turning in her purse was the quickest to one of the big exp chunks.  My rogue didn't need to do any faction building, but I don't know (yet) if there is anything to prevent other classes from doing it.  Of course the downside is Lynada is like a 4 or 8 hour spawn, so no power-levelling here, but it may be a nice bit of exp if you just are near SolA, first time logging on for the day, etc.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">cjd</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I just saw the thread from last year someone bumped.  Some of the posts there were interesting and along the lines I intended here.  Certainly if there is a quest that is super terrific like the thread on getting through the 50s or something, you'll want to keep it to yourself.  But there has to be plenty more quests one can do to pass time when you are bored from killing monsters and such, and still gives more than rat droppings in exp.<P>The most I have ever done through quick-questing was getting a character from 3-7 doing the Kaladim bone chip quest.  The down side was having to spend about two hours casting spells on himself to get the skills up.  A good balance of killing sometimes, and questing other times would make the game a bit better, away from the pure hack-n-heal/med.<P>Maintaining a database of the exp points is one interesting idea.  Are there any of the freeish web hosting sites that might give one a few megs of hd space and allow CGI scripts?  Sourceforge, perhaps?  With enough input, there may be some sort of formula for figuring when the exp peaks and drops off as you level to determine more exactly what level range the quest is good for.<P>Other thoughts?<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">il128</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The GLS quest is more easily done in Oasis.<BR>Just hand them in to Synthan(*?* female on the nro side of the camp.) at the gypsy camp.  <P>------------------<BR>il128<BR>I'm a pessimist or a realist.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">FrozenInTime</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The amount for a quest may go up each level because you are too low to receive the full benefit.  Quests and kills are locked so that no matter what, a character can only get something like 11% of a level from the completion of a single kill/quest (this doesn't mean you can't do the quest multiple times).  They did this to prevent true powerleveling with quests/kills (e.g. a lvl 1 kills a lvl 20 and jumps to lvl 3 right away.  Then does it again to get to most of the way through 4 etc...<P>Level equations:<BR>Total exp needed to clear a level<BR>Level * Level * Level * Race * Level Modifier<BR>Level Modifier == <BR>1; Level &lt; 30<BR>1.1; Level &lt; 35<BR>1.2; Level &lt; 40<P>etc...<P><BR>Exp per kill:<BR>Level * Level * ZEM</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">cjd</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yes, we all know about the maximum amounts of exp you can get.  The other thread said something like 11% for a kill and 16% for a quest.  With quests like some of the crafted armor pieces giving 200,000 points, sure a level 1 person should not get all that.<P>But things like the Kaladim bone chip quest give like low 3000s/high 2000s at level 3, then go up a few points each level to around 3750 at their peak at level 5 or 6.  Then once you hit a level past that peak, it comes down a tad to like 3200.  And a bit more at 8, and so on.  So the quest then becomes pointless as you aren't getting a worthwhile return.<P>Whenever there are mentions of this quest, people usually bring up the lego pad quest to do after bone chip quest is not worth it.  Is it just me or is this quest fairly futile as well?  It gives a bit more exp (around 7000, basically one level 10 kill's worth), but getting the pads is a huge hassle.  People want 1-2pp each (versus 1-2pp for a stack of bone chips, worth five quests).  To get through complete levels, you'd have to buy like 50 pads or so.  Not to mention the trouble finding that many on the market.  When I've leveled characters around Faydwer and was killing orcs in Crushbone, I could do more with the 2p or whatever from selling the pads than the little exp the quest gives.  Or am I just crazy?</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
